  "text": "For systemic depletion of DCs, DTR ϩ (age 12 to 16 weeks) or DTR ϩ Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ (age 10 to 12 weeks) mice were injected intraperitoneally with DT (4 ng/g body weight, in PBS; List Biologicals). Hypercholesterolemia was induced in 10-to 12-week-old Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ mice by replacing normal chow with CRD (40% fat, 1.25% cholesterol; diet D12108, Research Diets Inc). [CITATION_1] In some experiments, this was immediately after treatment with DT or PBS. Control groups included DTR ϩ Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ mice injected with PBS and DTR Ϫ Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ mice injected with DT. When determining lesion area after 5 days CRD feeding, control groups were combined because statistically significant differences between them were not observed.",
